Description:
Rector of the Kuban State University. Signed an open letter of university rectors expressing support for the decision of the President of Russia to launch a military operation against Ukraine.
Authorized representative of presidential candidate Vladimir Putin in the non-competitive presidential elections on March 15-17, 2024. Authorized representatives voluntarily campaign for the re-election of Vladimir Putin, who is responsible for unleashing an aggressive war against Ukraine and political repression in Russia.

Information from Vladimir Putin's election website:
Federal State Budgetary Educational Institution of Higher Education "Kuban State University", rector.
----
 
Deputy Chairman of the Council of Rectors of Universities of the Krasnodar Territory and the Republic of Adygea;
Member of the board of the Ministry of Education, Science and Youth Policy of the Krasnodar Territory;
Member of the commission under the head of the Administration (governor) of the Krasnodar Territory for the formation and training of reserves of managerial personnel;
Member of the Public Council under the Ministry of Education, Science and Youth Policy of the Krasnodar Territory;
Member of the Public Council under the Federal Tax Service of Russia for the Krasnodar Territory;
Member of the Presidium of the Krasnodar Regional Football Federation, chairman of the committee for work with educational institutions.

Actively and publicly supported Russian aggression against Ukraine.

Member of the Federation Council of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation (upper house of the federal parliament). Member of the Federation Council Committee on Defense and Security;
representative from the executive body of government of the Khabarovsk Territory. This state body is responsible for the political and legal support of the aggressive war against Ukraine, which included issuing permission for the use of Russian military forces outside the territory of Russia.

Former head of the Department of the Federal Security Service of Russia in the Khabarovsk Krai, a federal state body that carries out political persecution in the territory under its jurisdiction against citizens and organizations that oppose Russia's aggressive war against Ukraine and are in opposition to the current political regime in Russia. Dismissed from his position no later than July 25, 2022.
